{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ὑφαίνω</b> [ῠ], <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> <i>imperfect</i> ὑφαίνεσκον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 19.149 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>future</i> ὑφᾰνῶ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 654 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ὕφηνα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.739, 13.303, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 586, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; later ὕφᾱνα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Judg.16.14, “Inscription Délos” 442 A 206 (2nd c.BC), “Anthologia Graeca” 6.265 (3rd c.BC(?): Nossis Epigrammatica), “Hymnus ad Isim” 14\">LXX+3rd c.BC+</a>]; as <i>Doric dialect</i> form, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 5.9, +others: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>perfect</i> ὕφαγκα (συν-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Compositione Verborum” 18, (παρ-) Philo Byzantius Paradoxographus “de Septem Miraculis” 2.5 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, see below: <i>aorist</i> ὑφηνάμην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 87b, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.11.6 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <i>aorist</i> ὑφάνθην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 72c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], (ἐν-, συν-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.203, 5.105 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> ὕφασμαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 99, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “VH” 1.18, (ἐν-) 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.47, (παρ-) 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 5.4.48 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], but <i>3rd.pers.</i>. <i>singular</i> ὕφανται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Sextus Empiricus Philosophus “adversus Mathematicos” 8.129 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; a form ὑφήφασμαι is cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 10th c.AD: Suidas Legal icographus, ὑφήφανται in 2nd c.AD: Phrynichus Atticista “Praeparatio Sophistica” p.32 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus, ὑφήφασται 4th-5th c.AD: Choeroboscus Grammaticus “Scholia in Theodosii Canones” 2.91 H., ὑφύφασται 4th-3rd c.BC: Zenodotus Grammaticus cited in “Etymologicum Magnum” 785.46, 12th c.AD: Eustathius Episcopus Thessalonicensis 1436.51: compare ἐξυφαίνω. [ῠ\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] except in augment tenses.]:—<b>weave,</b> frequently in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus, who always joins ἱστὸν ὑφαίνειν (compare ὑφάω), 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.456, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.104, +others; except in 13.108 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], φάρε᾽ ὑφαίνουσι; so ὑ. ὕφασμα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1417; χλαῖναν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 586; ἱμάτιον 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Hp.Mi.” 368c; ἐν εὐπήνοις ὑφαῖς ὑ. τι 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 814; ἐν Ἐκβατάνοισι ταῦθ᾽ ὑφαίνεται 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 1143 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀράχνια ὑ., of spiders, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 542a13, compare 623a8 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>weave, ply the loom,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.35; αἱ ὑφαίνουσαι 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Generatione Animalium” 717a36; αἴγειροι πτελέαι τε ἐΰσκιον ἄλσος ὕφαινον 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 7.8 (conjecture Heinsius for ἔφαινον)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:— <i>middle</i>, ἱμάτιον ὑφαίνεσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 87b, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.11.6f:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, λίθος ὑφαινομένη, i.e. asbestos, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 10.1.6. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>contrive, plan,</b> of all schemes, good or bad, which are craftily imagined, frequently in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus; πυκινὸν δόλον ἄλλον ὕφαινε 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.187; ἔνδοθι μῆτιν ὑ. 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.678 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐνὶ φρεσὶ μῆτιν ὑφήνας[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 739; μῆτιν ὕφαινε μετὰ φρεσίν 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 28, compare 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 16.51; δόλους καὶ μῆτιν ὑ. 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.422; μύθους καὶ μήδεα πᾶσιν ὑ. 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 3.212, compare 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Fragmenta” 3ii10 P. (_passive_)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ταῦθ᾽ ὕφηναν ἡμῖν ἐπὶ τυραννίδι this was <b>the plot they laid</b> against us to bring in tyranny, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 630; πάντα.. ἐκ φρενὸς ὑφάνασα “Hymnus ad Isim” 14 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Nicopho Comicus 5: but ὑφαίνεται\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] is <i>falsa lectio</i> for{ὑφαίνετε} in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Lyrica Adespota” cited in 5th c.AD: Stobaeus, Joannes 1.5.11 (see. Nauck “TGF” 2p.xx). \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> generally, <b>create, construct,</b> οἰκοδομήματα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Critias” 116b; ὄλβον 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.141 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; θεμείλια Φοῖβος ὑφαίνει he <b>lays</b> the foundation, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Hymnus in Apollinem” 57; κηρὸν ὑ. 3rd-4th c.AD: Tryphiodorus Epicus 536:\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, ἀναίμου ὑφανθέντος [τοῦ σπληνός] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 72c. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>compose, write,</b> ποικίλον ἄνδημα (<i>metaphorically</i> of an ode) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 179; ὕμνον 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 5.9. (ὑφ-αίνω, compare ὑφή, ὕφος, O 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>wefan</b> 'weave', Sanskrit <i>ubhnāti</i> 'hold together, cover, bind'.)","strongNumber":"G9605","accentedUnicode":"ὑφαίνω","shortDef":"to weave","mediumDef":"to weave","stepGloss":"to weave","stepTransliteration":"hufainō","_step_Type":"verb"}]}